1.2 Helper functions

load_data <- function( data_filename ){
  testing_data = 
      read_delim( data_filename ,
                  delim="\t") %>%
      mutate( Week = week( SpecDate ) ) %>%
      ##filter( Week >= 34 ) %>%
      mutate( positive = RefLabel == "pos" )

  cat( dim( testing_data ) )
  cat( colnames( testing_data ) )
  return( testing_data )
}

Calculate expected number of tests under group testing of n negative individuals and \(m\) positive individual, when testing in groups of \(k\), for a total of \(g=\lceil \frac{n+m}{k} \rceil\) groups.

expected_tests_montecarlo = function(n, m, k, replicates = 100){
  f = c(rep(T,m), rep(F,n))
  pl = ifelse(length(f)%%k == 0, 0, k- length(f)%%k)
  res = replicate(replicates,
    sum(apply(matrix(c(sample(f), 
                       rep(F, pl)), ncol=k, byrow=T), 
              1,
              any)))
  mean(res)*k+ceiling((n+m)/k)
}
evaluate_predictor = function(threshold, 
                              prediction, 
                              labels, 
                              k = 5,
                              replicates = 100){
  group_test = prediction<=threshold
  m = sum(subset(labels, group_test)) # number of positives
  n = sum(group_test) - m
  expected_tests_montecarlo(n, m, k, replicates) + # expected number of tests under group testing
    sum(!group_test) # number of individual tests
}

evaluate_predictor_range = function(prediction,
                                    labels,
                                    k = 5,
                                    replicates = 100,
                                    thgrid = NULL){
  thresholds = thgrid
  if(is.null(thgrid)){
    thresholds = sort(c(unique(prediction), Inf), decreasing = T)
  }
  data.frame(
    threshold=thresholds,
    expected_tests = sapply(thresholds,
                            evaluate_predictor,
                            prediction=prediction,
                            labels=labels,
                            k = k,
                            replicates = replicates)
  )
}
augment_metrics <- function( input_data , performance_data ){

  performance_data = performance_data
  model_predictions = prediction( input_data$SysPred,
                                  input_data$positive )
  
  model_predictions.npv = performance(model_predictions, "npv")
  performance_data$npv = model_predictions.npv@y.values[[1]]
  performance_data$npv[is.na(performance_data$npv)] = 1
  
  model_predictions.spec = performance(model_predictions, "spec")
  performance_data$spec = model_predictions.spec@y.values[[1]]
  
  model_predictions.rec = performance(model_predictions, "rec")
  performance_data$rec = model_predictions.rec@y.values[[1]]
  
  model_predictions.auc = performance(model_predictions, "tpr","fpr")
  performance_data$tpr = model_predictions.auc@y.values[[1]]
  performance_data$fpr = model_predictions.auc@x.values[[1]]
  
  performance_data$pp = 
    sapply( performance_data$threshold,
            function(x) sum(input_data$SysPred>x))
        
  performance_data$np = 
    sapply( performance_data$threshold,
            function(x) sum(input_data$SysPred<=x))
  
  performance_data$tp = with(performance_data, tpr*pn.tab["pos"])
  performance_data$fp = with(performance_data, fpr*pn.tab["neg"])
  performance_data$tn = with(performance_data, pn.tab["neg"]-fp)
  performance_data$acc = with(performance_data, (tp+tn)/sum(pn.tab))
  return( list( performance_data , model_predictions ) )
}

prodExpectedTests <-
   trainingPerformance %>%
  filter( threshold >= prodThreshold ) %>%
  arrange( threshold ) %>%
  slice( 1L ) %>%
  select( expected_tests ) %>%
  as.numeric()
minTestThreshold <-
  trainingPerformance$threshold[which.min(trainingPerformance$expected_tests)]

minTestExpectedTests <-
  min(trainingPerformance$expected_tests)

6 Analyze Weekly Performance on Subsequent Dataset

date()
## [1] "Mon Jun  7 15:52:52 2021"
expectedTestRanges <- NA
expectedRangesAtThreshold <- NA
for( wk in 34:47 ){
    weeklySubset <-
        testing_data %>%
        filter( Week == wk )
    expectedWeeklyRanges <-
           evaluate_predictor_range( weeklySubset$SysPred,
                                     weeklySubset$positive,
                                     replicates = maxRepls , 
                                     thgrid = NULL ) %>%
            mutate( Week = wk )
    augmentedMetrics <- augment_metrics( weeklySubset , expectedWeeklyRanges )
    expectedWeeklyRanges <- augmentedMetrics[[ 1 ]]
    testingModelPredictions <- augmentedMetrics[[ 2 ]]
    uniqLabsThisWeek <- nrow( weeklySubset )
    expectedWeeklyRangesAtThreshold <-
          expectedWeeklyRanges %>%
      filter( threshold >= prodThreshold ) %>%
          arrange( threshold ) %>%
          slice( 1L ) %>%
      mutate( `Testing Ratio` = expected_tests / uniqLabsThisWeek ) %>%
      mutate( ThresholdBin = "Prod" ) %>%
          full_join( expectedWeeklyRanges %>%
          filter( threshold >= minTestThreshold ) %>%
              arrange( threshold ) %>%
              slice( 1L ) %>%
          mutate( `Testing Ratio` = expected_tests / uniqLabsThisWeek ) %>%
          mutate( ThresholdBin = "MinTests" ) ,
          by = c("threshold", "expected_tests", "Week", "npv", "spec", "tpr", "fpr", "pp", "np", "tp", "fp", "tn", "acc" , "rec", "Testing Ratio" , "ThresholdBin") )
    if( wk == 34 ){
        expectedTestRanges <-
      expectedWeeklyRanges
        expectedRangesAtThreshold <-
        expectedWeeklyRangesAtThreshold
    } else {
        expectedTestRanges <-
            expectedTestRanges %>%
            full_join( expectedWeeklyRanges ,
          by = c("threshold", "expected_tests", "Week", "npv", "spec", "tpr", "fpr", "pp", "np", "tp", "fp", "tn", "acc" , "rec") )
       expectedRangesAtThreshold <-
            expectedRangesAtThreshold %>%
            full_join( expectedWeeklyRangesAtThreshold ,
          by = c("threshold", "expected_tests", "Week", "npv", "spec", "tpr", "fpr", "pp", "np", "tp", "fp", "tn", "acc" , "rec", "Testing Ratio" , "ThresholdBin") )
    }
}
